cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.SE, cs.PL

This paper proposes a method to improve the generalizability and interpretability of neural networks that learn programs from data. This topic is closely related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the ability to reason about the behavior of these models, which is relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper focuses on the use of recursion in neural architectures, which is a fundamental concept in programming languages (cs.PL).
